Sentencas: In the present study, LSGM (La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.8) powder has been synthesized using precipitation route followed by hydrothermal treatment.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sr2+ and Mg2+ doped LaGaO3 by co-precipitation method followed by hydrothermal treatment for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Quantitative phase analyses of different powders, have been done by Rietveld analyses of the XRD data and they reveal formation of single phase orthorhombic LSGM at 1400 degrees C, 8 h. Morphology of the calcined powder and microstructure of the sintered pellets are observed by transmission electron microscope (TEM) and scanning electron microscope (SEM), respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sr2+ and Mg2+ doped LaGaO3 by co-precipitation method followed by hydrothermal treatment for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Thermal analysis has been carried out to find out the thermal expansion co-efficient.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sr2+ and Mg2+ doped LaGaO3 by co-precipitation method followed by hydrothermal treatment for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Successive electrical characterization of the 99% dense sintered pellet has been done by impedance spectroscopic analysis.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sr2+ and Mg2+ doped LaGaO3 by co-precipitation method followed by hydrothermal treatment for solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: The diffused semicircles observed in the Nyquist plots have been simulated as (RQ)(RQ) circuit and the total ionic conductivity obtained is found to be the highest for LSGM synthesized by similar routes.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of Sr2+ and Mg2+ doped LaGaO3 by co-precipitation method followed by hydrothermal treatment for solid oxide fuel cell applications
